This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Eric Schultz on June 26, 2015, aboard Air Force One en route to Charleston, South Carolina. Schultz discusses the President's reaction to the Supreme Court ruling on gay marriage, the mood in the White House, and the broader political context surrounding the ruling. He also addresses questions about the recent terror attacks and the President's schedule in Charleston. Additionally, Schultz mentions the lawmakers and families the President will be meeting with, as well as upcoming events and meetings in the week ahead.